Nordex U.S. Unit Completes Its Biggest Wind Farm for BP, Sempra

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-07-14T16:23:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/nordex-s-u-s-division-completes-its-biggest-wind-project-in-colorado.html
Nordex SE (NDX1) ’s U.S. division completed
its largest project, a 150-megawatt wind farm in northeastern
Colorado jointly owned by units of  BP Plc (BP/)  and  Sempra Energy. (SRE)   Nordex USA Inc. finished the Cedar Creek 2 project for the
renewable power units, Sempra Generation and BP Wind Energy, in
Weld County, Colorado, Nordex SE said today in a statement.  The project will use 60 of Hamburg-based Nordex’s N90/2500
 wind turbines , each with a generating capacity of 2.5 megawatts.
Power will be bought by  Xcel Energy Inc. (XEL) ’s utility Public
Service Company of Colorado under a 25-year contract. Nordex
will provide service and maintenance under a 5-year contract.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in  New York  at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net . 